Makeover Monday: Apr 09, 2018

Comments

I made a gif this week using the awesome gganimate package.

Code 

# libraries ----
library(data.world)
library(dplyr)
library(lubridate)
library(ggplot2)
library(gganimate)



# data import ----

# Datasets are referenced by their URL or path
dataset_key <- "https://data.world/makeovermonday/2018w15-arctic-sea-ice-extent"
# List tables available for SQL queries
tables_qry <- data.world::qry_sql("SELECT * FROM Tables")
tables_df <- data.world::query(tables_qry, dataset = dataset_key)

if (length(tables_df$tableName) > 0) {
  data_qry <- data.world::qry_sql(sprintf("SELECT * FROM `%s`", tables_df$tableName[[1]]))
  prelim_data <- data.world::query(data_qry, dataset = dataset_key)
}



# data preparation ----

dat <- prelim_data %>%
  arrange(date) %>%
  mutate(Year = year(date), doy = yday(date))



# plot ----

# time series plot
p <- ggplot(dat, aes(doy, extent_million_sq_km)) +
  geom_line(aes(frame = Year, cumulative = TRUE, group = Year), color = "gray80") +
  geom_line(aes(frame = Year, group = Year), color = "#08306b", size = 1.1) +
  scale_x_continuous(limits = c(0, 366), breaks = seq(0, 366, 30)) +
  scale_y_continuous(breaks = seq(0, 16, 2)) +
  ggtitle("Artic Sea Ice Extent") +
  labs(x = "Days Since Beginnning of Year",
       y = "Extent (Millions of Square Kilometers)",
       caption = "Source: National Snow & Ice Data Center") +
  theme_minimal() +
  theme(plot.caption = element_text(hjust = 0, size = 16),
        panel.grid.minor = element_blank(),
        plot.title = element_text(size = 18),
        axis.title = element_text(size = 16),
        axis.text = element_text(size = 14))

# gif
gganimate(p, filename = "output.gif", interval = 1.0, ani.width=1000, ani.height=600)
